I disagree...in case (1) [BBN] if you can't deliver directly to the host and it
has near neighbors that can handle mail it is reasonable to deliver the message
to the Forwarding host...after all you are then free of it.  The people who have
to be careful about using MF records like that are the listed forwarding hosts,
since it would be possible to get a one node mail loop that way.

